num_plot_rows = len(sahand.altitude.unique())

sahand_plot = (p9.ggplot(data=sahand, mapping=p9.aes(x='factor(date)', y='snow')) 
                + p9.geom_bar(stat="identity") # position = "dodge"
                + p9.facet_wrap('~ altitude', nrow=num_plot_rows)
                
                + p9.theme(axis_text_x=p9.element_text(size=8, angle=45))
                + p9.theme(figure_size=(15, 15))
               )

# secondary axis as in ggplot2 (future plotnine version ...):
#     scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~./200))

# === Add second axis for wind speed ===
sahand_fig, sahand_ax = sahand_plot.draw(return_ggplot=True)

axs = sahand_ax.axs

row = 0
for alt in sahand.altitude.unique(): #range(0, num_plot_rows):
    sub_df = sahand.query('altitude=='+str(alt))
    ax2 = axs[row].twinx() # here is the trick!
    ax2.plot(sub_df.date, sub_df.wind_speed, 'r--') # 'r.', 'r--'
    ax2.set_ylabel('wind (km/h)', color='r')
    ax2.tick_params('y', colors='r')
    row += 1

sahand_fig.tight_layout()

plt.show()

data_mid_level = weather_data.query('altitude in' + str([4909, 3105])) 
# data_mid_level.date = pd.to_datetime(data_mid_level.date, format='%Y-%m-%d').dt.strftime('%d.%m')

num_plot_rows = len(data_mid_level.altitude.unique())

mid_level_plot = (p9.ggplot(data=data_mid_level, mapping=p9.aes(x='factor(date)', y='snow')) 
                + p9.geom_bar(stat="identity") # position = "dodge"
                + p9.facet_wrap('~ resort + altitude', nrow=num_plot_rows)
                # + p9.scale_x_date(date_labels="%d.%m", date_breaks='1 day') 
                + p9.xlab("date")
                + p9.ylab("snow (cm)")
               
                # + p9.geom_text(p9.aes(label='snow'))
               
                + p9.theme(axis_text_x=p9.element_text(size=8, angle=45))
                + p9.theme(figure_size=(15, 15))
               )

# secondary axis as in ggplot2 (future plotnine version ...):
#     scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~./200))

# === Add second axis for wind speed ===
ml_fig, ml_ax = mid_level_plot.draw(return_ggplot=True)

axs = ml_ax.axs

row = 0
for alt in data_mid_level.altitude.unique(): #range(0, num_plot_rows):
    sub_df = data_mid_level.query('altitude=='+str(alt))
    # sub_df.date = pd.to_datetime(sub_df.date, format='%Y-%m-%d') #.dt.strftime('%d.%m')
    
    ax2 = axs[row].twinx() # here is the trick!
    ax2.plot(sub_df.date, sub_df.wind_speed, 'b--') # 'r.', 'r--'
    ax2.set_ylabel('wind (km/h)', color='b')
    ax2.tick_params('y', colors='b')
    
    ax1 = axs[row].twinx() # here is the trick!
    ax1.plot(sub_df.date, sub_df.temperature, 'r-') # 'r.', 'r--'
    ax1.set_ylabel('temperature (°C)', color='r')
    ax1.tick_params('y', colors='r')
    
    row += 1
    

ml_fig.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('damavand_sahand_mid_level.pdf')
plt.savefig('damavand_sahand_mid_level.png')
plt.show()

alt_levels = weather_data.altitude.unique()
alt_categories = [4909, 3105]

data_ = weather_data.query('altitude in' + str([4909, 3105])) # weather_data[weather_data.altitude.isin(alt_categories)]
snow_plot = (p9.ggplot(data=data_, mapping=p9.aes(x='factor(date)', y='snow')) 
             + p9.geom_bar(stat="identity", width=.3) # position = "dodge"
             + p9.facet_wrap('~ resort + altitude', nrow=len(alt_levels))
                
             + p9.theme(text=p9.element_text(size=11)) # , title=p9.element_text(size=16, face="bold")
             + p9.theme(axis_title=p9.element_text(size=14))   
             + p9.theme(axis_text_x=p9.element_text(size=10, angle=45),
                        strip_text_x=p9.element_text(size=12, face="italic"), # ,face="bold"
                       )  
             + p9.scale_x_date(date_labels="%d-%m", date_breaks='1  day') 
             + p9.xlab("date")
             + p9.ylab("snow (cm)")
             + p9.theme(figure_size=(15, 15))
            )

snow_plot.save('snow_plot_mid_level.pdf')
